claim.claim-text:
5. A method of manufacturing a thin-film coil, comprising the steps of: 
forming a first coil having a predetermined number of winding via a first insulating film; 
forming a second insulating film on a surface of the first coil and between its winding portions; 
forming an underlying conductive film on the second insulating film, and treating the underlying conductive film so as to leave only its bottom portions between the winding portions of the first coil; and 
growing deposition originating from a remaining portion of the underlying conductive film on the bottom portions between the winding portions of the first coil so as to form a second coil.

10. A method of manufacturing a magnetic head, comprising the steps of: 
forming a first coil having a predetermined number of winding via a first insulating film; 
forming a second insulating film on a surface of the first coil and between its winding portions; 
forming an underlying conductive film on the second insulating film, and treating the underlying conductive film so as to leave only its bottom portions between the winding portions of the first coil; and 
growing deposition originating from a remaining portion of the underlying conductive film on the bottom portions between the winding portions of the first coil so as to form a second coil.
